subject: 3 tips from prior winners - don't do the last one...
snippet: This was sent to you by EasyA We asked previous EasyA hackathon winners for their top 3 tips for you. Together, they've walked away on Sunday evening with a combined >$100k+ in their pockets. So
body:
Eventbrite








**** Eventbrite ****
--------------------


This was sent to you by EasyA

        


        
We asked previous EasyA hackathon winners for their top 3 tips for you. Together, they've walked away on Sunday evening with a combined >$100k+ in their pockets. So listen up - here they are!  1. "Ask questions. Before the mentors leave for the night, ask them tons of questions that might help you. Most people will leave this until midnight when most of the mentors have left. Don't be one of them"  2. "Find the judges. Ask every single one of them what they're interested in and excited to see you build. Form a relationship with them and show them why you're the type of people who will make this succeed (e.g. you're going to continue working on the idea after the hackathon). This is my secret formula to winning"  3. "Don't give up. So many teams just give up last minute. Don't do that. Just submit your project. If you're struggling, so is everyone else. Ngl one time I literally bluffed and won. The fact is, it's a hackathon. Nobody's perfect. Teams better than us thought we were geniuses, so they folded. They should've called our bluff"  Personally, I'm not so sure about that last one, but they're definitely right that you should just submit! After all, it's a 2-day hackathon. The judges understand you're not going to be anywhere near perfect!   — Phil
